	<ThingDef ParentName="BaseHumanMakeableGun">
        <defName>GW_Rulers_MeltaGun</defName>
        <label>Astartes melta gun</label>
        <description>A Melta weapon scaled for use by Space Marines in Power Armor. Melta weapons work either by sub-atomic agitation (causing the target to rapidly heat up and melt) or by projecting a small fusion reaction’s energy as a concentrated blast. The end result is a shot that has little range, but can melt Space Marine Terminators and battle tanks into slag. \n\nMelta weapons are surprisingly quiet - the majority of the noise being created by the target vaporizing - so they can be used by infiltrators to destroy enemy vehicles in ambushes and stealth strikes. They are also effective in close-range anti-tank and anti-Marine fighting - woe betide the tanker or Astartes that underestimates a “mere mortal” with a Melta gun. \n\nWhile they are not strictly called Melta weapons, similar weapons can be seen in the service of the Eldar, the Dark Eldar, the T’au, and the Necrons.</description>
